他们虽然英语都说得很好，可是我并没有听到他们谈什么。两人总是喜欢站在一起，整夜用古怪的锡克语嘀哩嘟噜地说个不停。我常是一个人站在堡门外，向下望着那宽阔而弯曲的河流和那大城里闪烁的灯火。

[07:32.87]The beating of drums, the rattle of tomtoms, and the yells and howls of the rebels, drunk with opium and with bang, were enough to remind us all night of our dangerous neighbours across the stream.  Every two hours the officer of the night used to come round to all the posts to make sure that all was well. 
咚咚的鼓声和印度铜锣的声音，吸足了鸦片的叛军们的狂喊乱叫，整夜里都提醒着我们：河对面有着危险的邻人。每隔两点钟就有值夜的军官到各岗哨巡查一次，以防意外。 

[07:45.23]"The third night of my watch was dark and dirty, with a small driving rain.  It was dreary work standing in the gateway hour after hour in such weather.  I tried again and again to make my Sikhs talk, but without much success. 
